{
  "stem": "3040.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they were leading me to the-- yeah, what-- what was left after the liquidation of the ghetto was the jail.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Because they were-- they were catching people every day on false papers, like myself, or people hiding in the bunkers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And they were putting, you know, they're keeping on this jail for-- for-- for-- to be able to accommodate these people who they're catching on the-- on false papers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And there were some Jewish policemen in charge of that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They called them Ordnungsdienst in German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "They were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "They were in uniforms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "They're working for the Germans, and they were taking care of the jail.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "While they were leading me, when we were walking, there was this [? kommando ?] going back, after the day's work, going back to the Plaszow concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And my brother, who was in that-- in that company, in that, you know, in that [? kommando, ?] which is going to the-- to work in the-- in the ghetto, saw me-- saw me and that these-- these two Germans are leading me.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So many strange coincidences.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's not that they could do anything about me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of-- the-- the brother that lives now in Israel, he saw me actually walking with these two Germans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The next day, he came down again with the [? kommando ?] to work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he tried to get in touch with me in the jail, and he said, listen, I will try, maybe we can get you out, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nothing happened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So what did happen is, after day 6, the-- the jail was filled up to capacity.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They took-- they said, we are going to-- to-- we are going all to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, you will walk.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We'll march to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
